{
  "_meta": {
    "source": "Wong, C.H., Siah, K.W., Lo, A.W. (2019). Estimation of clinical trial success rates and related parameters. Biostatistics 20(2), 273-286. doi:10.1093/biostatistics/kxx069",
    "sample": "406,038 trial entries / 185,994 unique trials / 21,143 compounds, Jan 1 2000 - Oct 31 2015. Industry-sponsored analysis: 41,040 development paths (67,752 phase transitions).",
    "phase_scheme": "Wong tracks THREE transitions: Phase 1->2, Phase 2->3, Phase 3->Approval. Unlike BIO/QLS (2021), Wong does NOT split out the regulatory NDA/BLA->Approval step, so 'pos3_app' spans BOTH filing and approval. Keys: pos1_2, pos2_3, pos3_app, pos2_app (Phase 2 -> Approval), loa (= POS1,APP, overall Phase 1 -> Approval). Do NOT equate pos3_app with BIO/QLS 'phase3_to_filing'.",
    "methods": "path-by-path is Wong's headline method (Tables 1, 2, 4). phase-by-phase is used for the biomarker analysis (Table 3) and the prior-literature comparison columns of Table 1. Rates stored as fractions.",
    "known_discrepancy": "The paper's abstract/body text states 'POS2,3 = 58.3%', but Table 1 and Table 2 report the all-indications path-by-path POS2,3 as 48.6% (58.3% is actually the Infectious-disease group value). We treat the TABLE value (0.486) as authoritative. Recorded per the brief's Day-4 'document, do not silently reconcile' guidance.",
    "notes": "N.A. cells (very small samples) are recorded as null. The all-indications phase-by-phase column of Table 1 is intentionally omitted: its reading was internally inconsistent (POS1,APP did not equal the product of the phase POS), and Wong's path-by-path figures are the headline estimates used for cross-validation."
  },

